ABUJA – The Federal Govern­ment has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Mota- Engil Group on the construction of the $1.959 billion Kano-Maradi (Repub­lic of Niger) standard gauge railway lines. Rt. Hon. Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi, the Minister of Transportation, on Monday, in Abuja, signed on behalf of the Federal Government while the Managing Director, Mota-Engil, Antonio Gvoea, signed on behalf of the con­tracting firm. Eric Ojiekwe, Director, Press and Public Relations, in a statement, noted that the new railway corridor, which is to be located in Northern Nigeria, will run through three states, Kano, Jigawa, and Katsina, and through Ni­ger territory as far as Maradi. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Other cities that would be affected by the rail line in Ni­geria are Danbatta, Kazaure, Daura, Mashi, Katsina, and Jibiya. The 283.750 kilometres rail line, besides developing freight and passenger trans­port as it would be integrated with road transport, would make a great contribution to the local economy as well as an important development in the social sector. Acting Homeland Security Secretary Chad Wolf To Step Down Ugandans Warned Not To Eat Dead Fish Washed Ashore The project duration is 36 months and the contract type is Engineering, Procurement and Construction. The signing ceremony was witnessed by the Per­manent Secretary, Federal Ministry of Transportation, Dr. Magdalene Ajani, and the Director, Legal Services, Pius Oteh; the Managing Director, Mota-Engil Group, Antonio Gvoea; Head of Legal, Mo­ta-Engil Group, Cameron Beverley; Magajin Garin Kano, Muhammad Wada; Director, Mota-Engil Group, Kola Abdulkarim; Vice Pres­ident, Mota-Engil Group, Mohammed Abdul-Razaq; Nigerian Ambassador to Germany, Yusfu Tuggar; the Managing Director, Nigeri­an Ports Authority, Hadiza Bala-Usman, among other dignitaries.